{"repository":{"pullRequests":{"edges":[{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvZmCg==","node":{"additions":44,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>This ensures the mixed <code>notFound</code>/<code>redirect</code> error is shown correctly and adds an err.sh for the error.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18727.\">Closes</span>: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"735187215\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18727\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/18727/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18727\">#18727</a></p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T21:36:38Z","deletions":2,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19076,"state":"OPEN","title":"Add test and errsh for mixed notFound/redirect error","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19076","comments":{"totalCount":0},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"ijjk","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/22380829?u=a5bee349128d0372211ebea25c8b8e1faf5afae4&v=4","url":"https://github.com/ijjk","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvXr1w==","node":{"additions":3,"authorAssociation":"NONE","bodyHTML":"<p>I believe this should read <a href=\"https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/altogether\" rel=\"nofollow\">\"altogether\"</a> not \"all together\".</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T20:27:26Z","deletions":3,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19072,"state":"OPEN","title":"Fix grammar in isSerializableProps","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19072","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"aried3r","avatarUrl":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1301152?v=4","url":"https://github.com/aried3r","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvW03Q==","node":{"additions":74,"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","bodyHTML":"<ul>\n<li>upgrading node-sass lets you build next with Python 3<br>\nnode-sass v4 requires an old version of node-gyp to build, which requires Python 2 which reached EOL in April 2020</li>\n<li>the node-sass major version bump is mainly for removing support for Node &lt; 10; next requires 10.13 anyway</li>\n<li>node-sass release notes <a href=\"https://github.com/sass/node-sass/releases/tag/v5.0.0\">https://github.com/sass/node-sass/releases/tag/v5.0.0</a></li>\n</ul>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T19:58:38Z","deletions":129,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19070,"state":"OPEN","title":"Bump node-sass development dep to v5","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19070","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"ludofischer","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/43557?u=6726c9c53c96e354eac705c05e5ea9161970b3b9&v=4","url":"https://github.com/ludofischer","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvQ7MQ==","node":{"additions":463,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>This fixes a few things related to optional catch-all routes and i18n. The first thing is it ensures the correct data route is generated on the client so that the locale isn't duplicated for an optional catch-all route, the next is it ensures the browser history is updated correctly when only a locale change is occurring, and then it also ensures we handle the locales and normalizing for fallback optional catch-all pages correctly.</p>\n<p>Tests have been added to ensure these cases are covered properly and we don't regress on them, these changes were also tested on Vercel <a href=\"https://next-js-bug-i18n-root-params-nybg44l0b.vercel.app/\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a></p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18633.\">Fixes</span>: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"734036070\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18633\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/18633/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18633\">#18633</a><br>\n<span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #19059.\">Fixes</span>: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"740840706\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/19059\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/19059/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/19059\">#19059</a></p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T16:49:26Z","deletions":12,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-11T20:33:45Z","number":19063,"state":"MERGED","title":"Ensure params and locale are parsed correctly in fallback mode","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19063","comments":{"totalCount":5},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":1}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"ijjk","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/22380829?u=a5bee349128d0372211ebea25c8b8e1faf5afae4&v=4","url":"https://github.com/ijjk","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvNxGw==","node":{"additions":539,"authorAssociation":"NONE","bodyHTML":"<p>Add an example for using Next.js with Deta Base on Vercel.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T15:25:10Z","deletions":0,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19061,"state":"OPEN","title":"Example: Deta Base","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19061","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"xeust","avatarUrl":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/7769878?u=d354687987d3f7b4c96146c4d5d412a190be9a04&v=4","url":"https://github.com/xeust","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvL9Xw==","node":{"additions":2,"authorAssociation":"NONE","bodyHTML":"","createdAt":"2020-11-11T14:39:49Z","deletions":2,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19056,"state":"OPEN","title":"fixed project name to reflect example name in readme","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19056","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"pocorschi","avatarUrl":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/233198?v=4","url":"https://github.com/pocorschi","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHvICIA==","node":{"additions":51,"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","bodyHTML":"<p>The current <code>&lt;Image /&gt;</code> component does not fallback gracefully when JavaScript is disabled in the client / browser.</p>\n<p>You can test this with the <a href=\"https://csb-4k0kr-p8ya8f304.vercel.app/\" rel=\"nofollow\">official Next/Image example</a>, by disabling JavaScript in the browser's DevTools. Video demo: <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://streamable.com/frkvw9\">https://streamable.com/frkvw9</a></p>\n<p>This PR aims to fix this behaviour by using <code>&lt;noscript&gt;&lt;/noscript&gt;</code> tags to conditionally display a standard <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> element using the <code>props</code> passed to <code>&lt;Image /&gt;</code> when JavaScript is disabled.</p>\n<p>For browser sessions where JavaScript is enabled, this will not cause an increase in network requests, so there should be no downside.</p>\n<p>One area where this PR is a bit \"hacky\" is that it uses a negative <code>margin-top</code> to counteract <code>sizerStyle.paddingTop</code>. From what I can tell, <code>sizerStyle.paddingTop</code> is generated on the server side, where we can not know ahead of time whether JavaScript is enabled in the browser - hence why I've opted for this solution.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T12:48:09Z","deletions":34,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19052,"state":"OPEN","title":"Add fallback for <Image /> component when JavaScript is disabled in browser","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19052","comments":{"totalCount":0},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":4}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"brunocrosier","avatarUrl":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/18399089?u=cd99087f9410ecdc2df03e599cfce22aeb6db794&v=4","url":"https://github.com/brunocrosier","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHu2BBw==","node":{"additions":61,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>This ensures we use the <code>defaultLocale</code> for a locale domain when rendering non-static pages. Static pages will initially contain the global <code>defaultLocale</code> and then be updated on the client since we don't currently prerender a version of the pages for each locale domain.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18970.\">Closes</span>: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"738859338\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18970\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/18970/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18970\">#18970</a></p>","createdAt":"2020-11-11T01:48:55Z","deletions":8,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-11T02:09:46Z","number":19040,"state":"MERGED","title":"Ensure correct defaultLocale is provided for locale domain","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19040","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"ijjk","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/22380829?u=a5bee349128d0372211ebea25c8b8e1faf5afae4&v=4","url":"https://github.com/ijjk","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuxBDg==","node":{"additions":19,"authorAssociation":"NONE","bodyHTML":"<p>Added showDefaultLocale option in the i18n config so that the developer can decide if the default locale should part of the Sub-path or not.</p>\n<p>For discussion <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"28804\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419\" data-hovercard-type=\"discussion\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419\">#18419</a> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"28804\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419\" data-hovercard-type=\"discussion\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/18419\">#18419</a></p>\n<p>I personally think that it would be nice when we have this option because we currently rebuild our Webshop with Next.js and this is one feature we need so that we can use the next.js internal i18n solution.</p>\n<p>#myfirstpr #pleasebenice :D</p>\n<p>Thanks for consideration<br>\nRobin</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T22:22:29Z","deletions":2,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19035,"state":"OPEN","title":"Add showDefaultLocale option for i18n so that the we can show the def…","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19035","comments":{"totalCount":4},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":1}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"RobinSCU","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/50205066?u=511fe91b56f25cc3d893c9bfd09ce42ae7e270e5&v=4","url":"https://github.com/RobinSCU","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuw_uA==","node":{"additions":1,"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","bodyHTML":"<p>Changed function name from \"getStaticProps\" to \"getStaticPaths\" in Exception message thrown when 'paths' is invalid.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T22:21:41Z","deletions":1,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-10T23:53:09Z","number":19034,"state":"MERGED","title":"Fixed wrong function name in error message","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19034","comments":{"totalCount":3},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"lyderichti59","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/34691216?u=4c108b71998e539c9bed0d049c9935c8eb318eba&v=4","url":"https://github.com/lyderichti59","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuwOzQ==","node":{"additions":143,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18356.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"731016402\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18356\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/18356/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18356\">#18356</a></p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T21:54:13Z","deletions":1,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-11T15:46:49Z","number":19032,"state":"MERGED","title":"Print error during `next export` with default image loader","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19032","comments":{"totalCount":5},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"styfle","avatarUrl":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/229881?u=95ef292ae4de28398c06ec6619f00d546bd3032f&v=4","url":"https://github.com/styfle","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHunLBA==","node":{"additions":18,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>We fixed this in a previous PR but there were no tests for <code>.ico</code> so this PR adds a test for it to ensure we don't regress.</p>\n<p>Similar to SVG, we bypass ICO because it typically contains multiple sizes in a single file.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18600.\">Closes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"733854119\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18600\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/vercel/next.js/issues/18600/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/18600\">#18600</a></p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T17:11:09Z","deletions":0,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-10T17:49:38Z","number":19025,"state":"MERGED","title":"Add test for `.ico` image bypass","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19025","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"styfle","avatarUrl":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/229881?u=95ef292ae4de28398c06ec6619f00d546bd3032f&v=4","url":"https://github.com/styfle","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHujFpw==","node":{"additions":12,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>This PR moves the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element inside the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> element.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T15:29:59Z","deletions":12,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-10T17:02:40Z","number":19022,"state":"MERGED","title":"Fix ViewSource component in the docs","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19022","comments":{"totalCount":10},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"styfle","avatarUrl":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/229881?u=95ef292ae4de28398c06ec6619f00d546bd3032f&v=4","url":"https://github.com/styfle","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuX6Gg==","node":{"additions":1,"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","bodyHTML":"<p>If the example is cloned and ran with no further setup (no environment variables set up), it will error out because <code>extractPostEntries</code> will return <code>undefined</code> which can not be serialized by <code>getStaticProps </code>.</p>\n<p>This PR basically ensures that we return an empty array instead of the <code>undefined</code> for a collection of posts, and a <code>null</code> instead of the <code>undefined</code> for a single post.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T10:33:49Z","deletions":1,"merged":true,"mergedAt":"2020-11-10T23:33:52Z","number":19012,"state":"MERGED","title":"[Examples] Prevent getStaticProps from returning \"undefined\"","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19012","comments":{"totalCount":4},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"OriginalEXE","avatarUrl":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/2056251?u=d1ea981f52fa7acd89dc2fc87040797db8e59887&v=4","url":"https://github.com/OriginalEXE","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuSA3g==","node":{"additions":11,"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","bodyHTML":"<p>Leverage <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/execa\">execa</a> for writing to <code>stdin</code>.</p>","createdAt":"2020-11-10T07:43:30Z","deletions":22,"merged":false,"mergedAt":null,"number":19008,"state":"OPEN","title":"tests(create-next-app): leverage execa","url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/19008","comments":{"totalCount":1},"reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"LAUGH","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HOORAY","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"CONFUSED","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"ROCKET","users":{"totalCount":0}},{"content":"EYES","users":{"totalCount":0}}],"author":{"login":"jamesgeorge007","avatarUrl":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/25279263?u=4b3389d9cd2e2aa0eab21899cb7e5746a4889e31&v=4","url":"https://github.com/jamesgeorge007","__typename":"User"}}},{"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOHuQw7g==","node":{"additions":545,"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","bodyHTML":"<p>This pull request completely replaces our old page loader with a brand new route loader.</p>\n<p>Our existing comprehensive test suite means I did not need to add a bunch of tests. I did add them where behavior was added or fixed.</p>\n<p>Summary of the changes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Eagerly evaluates prefetched pages in browser idle time (speeds up transitions)</li>\n<li>Router is <strong>no longer frozen</strong> indefinitely if the Build Manifest never arrives</li>\n<li>Router is <strong>no longer frozen</strong> indefinitely if a page fails to bootstrap</li>\n<li>New <code>withFuture</code> utility instead of ad-hoc deduping per resource</li>\n<li>Prefetching is now delayed until browser idle time to not impact TTI</li>\n<li>Browsers without <code>prefetch</code> now fall back to eager evaluation instead of using <code>preload</code></li>\n<li>We're now ready to serve non-static assets <strong>with <code>no-store</code> without breaking prefetching</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Application can now hydrate without fetching CSS assets—this is a huge performance win that was previously blocking hydration</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>The minor size increase here is unfortunate, but we have to incur it for correctness.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #18389.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link j